description.value: The fabulous neighborhood of Fairmount is known for its proximity to the Parkway and its world-renowned cultural institutions, easy access to the Schuylkill River Trail, all the recreation Fairmount Park has to offer, and a lively shopping and restaurant scene. Be welcomed home by the trees lining this handsome block of historic brick homes, uniquely ornamented with ceramic and decorative masonry details. Arriving at the entry of your first floor, be welcomed into a modern open floor plan with gleaming hardwood floors and oversized windows bathing the living area in natural light. In fact, if you’re looking to be bathed in glorious natural light, you’ve come to the right place. The morning light streams in from the east through oversized windows in every room and even the hallways. Counting an amazing bay window in the 2nd-floor bedroom, there are 22 total windows in this home. Continue past the formal dining room into a fabulous stainless and stone chef's kitchen with a fun breakfast bar that adds to the surplus of linear counter space, creating a perfect setup for entertaining guests while you showcase your culinary skills preparing a gourmet meal. Past the kitchen, there's an adorable powder room, laundry, and butler’s pantry for more than just added convenience. Beyond that, soak up the rays or dine alfresco on your own private paved patio, perfect for entertaining, grilling, and chilling. Downstairs, you will find an enormous unfinished basement providing a proverbial ton of storage and one of the two HVAC systems. Dual-zoned heat and air are the only way to go in a home this size. Up the charming original staircase, on the 2nd floor, find 2 of 3 bedrooms and a landing, naturally lit by another oversized window, currently set up as a home office that could otherwise be utilized as a cozy family room, home gym, meditation area, or den. Every bedroom in this home is spacious, outfitted with oversized closets, and custom blinds with top-down/bottom up capability and/or black out shades. A chic hall bathroom features plenty of space for multiple occupants with its double sink, fancy tiled niche, and serviced by a hall closet that also houses the 2nd HVAC. One more flight up the original staircase, pass a sunny alcove perfect for plants, to discover the expansive sunbathed, 3rd-floor primary suite topping this lovely home off with high ceilings, lots of closet space, and a luxurious spa-like master bath with double sinks, soaking tub, natural stone tile, and glass shower enclosure. This distinct and elegant home, nestled in a rich historical context, has it all and is bound to suit your lifestyle. Ditch your car! You’ll be walking only minutes to Whole Foods Market, The Barnes Museum, The Philadelphia Art Museum, or Kelly Drive. Even closer than that, there’s a fantastic Italian restaurant across the street and multiple coffee shops nearby, as well as a bar offering pub grub and a fenced in park for you and your pupperdoos (don’t just drop in, dogs and their vaccination records must be pre-registered, also 21+ only). Location, Location, Location AND partial tax abatement good through 2030.

description.value: Forget charming, spacious, and convenient - this sprawling 5-6 bedroom stone and Tudor masterpiece transcends mere adjectives.  It's a portal to a bygone era of meticulous craftsmanship and timeless artistry, interwoven with modern luxuries that pamper. Stepping onto the wrap-around porch and approaching the solid oak door is like entering a Downton Abbey dreamscape. An oak and terra cotta vestibule greets, then leads to a generous foyer, with ample space to shed coats before venturing into this architectural ode to sophistication. In the Living Room, thickly layered crown molding tops plaster walls, sunlight from a huge bank of windows glints off original floors, and built-in leaded glass bookcases beckon you to sit by the wood-burning fireplace with its vintage Mercer tile for a cozy evening enveloped in warmth and the spaciousness of this room. The grandeur doesn't stop there – a large Dining Room with another huge bank of windows, built-in leaded glass china cabinet, and, again, that multi-layered crown molding, plus contemporary sconces and chandelier, is perfect for entertaining on either an intimate or grand scale. But amidst the old-world charm, modernity calls. A renovated powder room in the foyer sparkles. A chef's dream kitchen awaits, with sleek cabinets, tumbled stone backsplash, granite countertops, and a Brizo Artesso faucet, like a piece of contemporary jewelry, that presides over this culinary playground. KitchenAid appliances hum, an island beckons, and a mudroom with cabinetry and counter space offers storage and access to the rear deck. Upstairs, the primary bedroom awaits, a huge sanctuary of calm and FOUR closets with mirrored doors, original floors, and an enormous bank of windows. A renovated en-suite bathroom with leaded glass windows is swathed in marble, sparkling heavyweight nickel hardware, and timeless gray and white. Two more ample bedrooms share a large vintage bathroom.  The third floor unfurls like an untapped story. The spacious landing on this floor is anchored by an enormous 5x7 walk-in closet and a bathroom, as smartly renovated as the 2nd-floor bath, in nickel and marble! One bedroom cradles a future nursery or office, another basks in sunshine, and a vast 26-foot-long third awaits your vision - perhaps a second suite, au pair haven, or rec room.  Outside, sunshine bathes the fenced yard, laughter echoing off ivy-covered walls. A spacious deck whispers of starlit evenings spent sipping wine and basking in the moonlit symphony of crickets. And, two dedicated parking spots ensure your chariot awaits, ready to whisk you to the vibrant heart of Center City. Perfectly situated, it is in the CW Henry Catchment and just a short walk to Weaver's Way Co-op, a bookstore, cafes, boutiques, and two train stations for easy access to Center City. It is also an easy train ride to NYC, Baltimore, or DC. Walk to Carpenter’s Woods, or any of the trailheads of Wissahickon Valley Park. Additionally, Mt Airy’s exceptional community offers festivals and events throughout the year, as well as access to every mover, shaker, and thought leader in Philadelphia. This isn't just a house; it's a tapestry woven from community, history, elegance, and modern comfort. It's a statement, a sanctuary, and a chapter waiting to be written by its next steward. Are you ready to step into a world where timeless beauty and modern comfort meet tranquil living and urban conveniences?  Then welcome home.
